00:25:00,365 --> 00:25:01,484
Long time no see.

249
00:25:01,811 --> 00:25:03,899
<i>This is my first time here.</i>

250
00:25:04,607 --> 00:25:05,816
Maybe I'm wrong.

251
00:25:06,031 --> 00:25:07,950
<i>But she looks familiar.</i>

252
00:25:09,522 --> 00:25:13,938
You look very familiar.
Have we met before?

253
00:25:14,632 --> 00:25:17,339
"Search for the Best Chef."

254
00:25:18,027 --> 00:25:20,850
"Thursdays at 6:30 on MBC."

255
00:25:20,852 --> 00:25:23,129
"The youngest female chef
of Japanese cuisine."

256
00:25:23,341 --> 00:25:24,390
Oh, that?

257
00:25:25,462 --> 00:25:28,848
They said the ratings are low,
but someone must watch it.

258
00:25:28,850 --> 00:25:32,569
Women's hands are usually warm,
so they cannot make sushi.

259
00:25:32,571 --> 00:25:35,118
Well, you certainly know your stuff.

260
00:25:48,487 --> 00:25:49,656
Who are you?

261
00:25:53,364 --> 00:25:55,131
Do you...

262
00:25:55,133 --> 00:25:56,392
like your clothes?

263
00:26:03,032 --> 00:26:04,401
Why?

264
00:26:06,819 --> 00:26:09,776
- Why did you imprison me?
- Who do you think I am?

265
00:26:12,161 --> 00:26:14,039
- Yoo Heung-sam?
- Wrong.

266
00:26:14,752 --> 00:26:17,919
- Did Lee So-young pay you?
- Wrong again.

267
00:26:18,637 --> 00:26:19,676
Lee Jong-yong?

268
00:26:20,735 --> 00:26:21,774
Kang Chang-suk?

269
00:26:22,812 --> 00:26:24,980
Hwang Joo-yeun? Kim Na-sung?

270
00:26:25,596 --> 00:26:29,274
Park Jin-woo? Im Duk-yoon?
Lee Jae-pyung? Kuk Su-ran?

271
00:26:29,276 --> 00:26:31,984
- Who the hell are you?
- Me?

272
00:26:32,522 --> 00:26:34,100
I'm a sort of scholar.

273
00:26:35,103 --> 00:26:36,772
And my field of study is you.

274
00:26:37,756 --> 00:26:39,603
A scholar studying Oh Dae-su.

275
00:26:40,235 --> 00:26:42,493
An expert on Oh Dae-su.

276
00:26:43,297 --> 00:26:46,415
Who I am isn't important.
What's important is "why".

277
00:26:46,417 --> 00:26:47,916
Think hard.

278
00:26:48,117 --> 00:26:50,075
Study your whole lifetime.

279
00:26:51,168 --> 00:26:54,635
School has finished,
now it's time for your homework.

280
00:26:56,802 --> 00:26:58,060
Keep this in mind:

281
00:26:59,156 --> 00:27:01,654
"Whether it be a grain
of sand or a rock,

282
00:27:02,198 --> 00:27:04,196
in water they both sink alike."

283
00:27:05,594 --> 00:27:06,973
Let me ask you one thing.

284
00:27:08,064 --> 00:27:11,891
You hypnotized me in there,
didn't you?

285
00:27:13,339 --> 00:27:14,678
What did you do to me?

286
00:27:15,915 --> 00:27:17,413
I miss you.

287
00:27:18,567 --> 00:27:19,435
Come quickly.

288
00:27:30,991 --> 00:27:33,028
Here you are.

289
00:27:36,636 --> 00:27:37,755
It's alive, OK?

290
00:27:39,543 --> 00:27:41,751
I'll go and slice it up for you.

291
00:28:17,798 --> 00:28:21,584
I must be a different breed of woman.
My hands are very cold.

292
00:28:23,309 --> 00:28:24,888
<i>What is she doing?</i>

293
00:28:30,462 --> 00:28:31,301
Sir.

294
00:28:32,748 --> 00:28:34,376
Sir, wake up.

295
00:28:36,710 --> 00:28:37,999
<i>Keep this in mind.</i>

296
00:28:39,661 --> 00:28:42,748
<i>"Whether it be a grain
of sand or a rock...</i>

297
00:28:43,794 --> 00:28:47,380
<i>...in water they both sink alike. "</i>

298
00:28:53,936 --> 00:28:55,434
Are you awake?

299
00:29:05,852 --> 00:29:07,310
Is all this true?

300
00:29:28,822 --> 00:29:30,610
That fever remedy works well.

301
00:29:32,541 --> 00:29:36,077
Why did you faint if you've done
so much physical training?

302
00:29:38,089 --> 00:29:43,714
A lack of vital sunlight leaves one
depleted of vitamins A and E.

303
00:29:45,934 --> 00:29:48,761
Thus, one's immunity to
influenza is weakened.

304
00:29:51,138 --> 00:29:53,016
Do you always talk like that?

305
00:30:06,201 --> 00:30:08,632
The lock on the
bathroom door is broken.

306
00:30:09,142 --> 00:30:10,641
Don't get any bright ideas

307
00:30:10,940 --> 00:30:12,858
or I'll gut you like a fish.

308
00:30:14,957 --> 00:30:15,996
What's this?

309
00:30:17,249 --> 00:30:21,375
Suppositories. You fainted, so
how else could I give you medicine?

310
00:30:36,482 --> 00:30:40,898
<i>Can 15 years' worth of
imaginary training be put to use?</i>

311
00:30:48,980 --> 00:30:50,108
<i>Apparently not.</i>

312
00:31:06,263 --> 00:31:08,181
That was an unforgivable sin.

313
00:31:12,303 --> 00:31:16,679
I brought you back here
and then turned you down.

314
00:31:17,483 --> 00:31:19,071
I can see why you're angry.

315
00:31:20,275 --> 00:31:21,524
I really can.

316
00:31:25,105 --> 00:31:29,111
You know, I brought you
here because I like you.

317
00:31:30,012 --> 00:31:31,171
But...

318
00:31:33,992 --> 00:31:36,069
You don't even know my name yet.

319
00:31:37,077 --> 00:31:38,236
It's Mido.

320
00:31:39,866 --> 00:31:41,074
You see...

321
00:31:42,615 --> 00:31:43,824
...later on...

322
00:31:45,566 --> 00:31:47,274
...when I'm really ready...

323
00:31:48,596 --> 00:31:51,303
...I swear on my life
that I'll go through with it.

324
00:31:52,988 --> 00:31:56,614
That song in your diary, "The Face
I Want to See", that will be the sign.

325
00:31:57,383 --> 00:32:02,258
When I sing it, get ready.

326
00:32:04,305 --> 00:32:10,809
I may try to resist you again
in the heat of the moment.

327
00:32:11,843 --> 00:32:14,260
But no matter what, don't stop.

328
00:32:14,416 --> 00:32:17,243
Just give it to me!

329
00:32:19,883 --> 00:32:21,051
<i>Give it...</i>

330
00:32:22,961 --> 00:32:24,419
<i>...to me.</i>

331
00:32:30,249 --> 00:32:31,798
The ants...

332
00:32:32,961 --> 00:32:34,329
Do you still see them?

333
00:32:35,489 --> 00:32:37,117
Do you still feel that way?

334
00:32:38,867 --> 00:32:42,203
Yeah, if you're alone, you see ants.

335
00:32:43,412 --> 00:32:48,579
People I have met who are very lonely
have all hallucinated about ants.

336
00:32:50,219 --> 00:32:52,227
I tried once to work out why.

337
00:32:52,403 --> 00:32:54,761
Ants move around in groups,
you know.

338
00:32:56,321 --> 00:33:00,327
So I suppose very lonely people
keep thinking of ants.

339
00:33:01,792 --> 00:33:04,249
Although I have never done that.

340
00:34:07,071 --> 00:34:12,117
She called from overseas five or six
years ago, asking if her dad had come back.

341
00:34:12,856 --> 00:34:16,772
She doesn't even know
that he killed her mother.

342
00:34:17,254 --> 00:34:20,753
She has hardly any relatives,
so she calls us.

343
00:34:22,142 --> 00:34:24,560
Her Korean has got worse.

344
00:34:26,409 --> 00:34:29,366
I think her Swedish foster
parents are both doctors.

345
00:34:32,486 --> 00:34:34,194
You journalists must know...

346
00:34:36,949 --> 00:34:38,917
Dae-su...

347
00:34:38,919 --> 00:34:41,416
Is he really still on the run?

348
00:34:45,950 --> 00:34:48,949
Your daughter's address
is on the front

349
00:34:48,951 --> 00:34:51,538
and on the back is a map
of your wife's grave.

350
00:34:55,528 --> 00:34:56,609
<i>Eva...</i>

351
00:34:57,484 --> 00:34:58,827
<i>Stockholm...</i>

352
00:34:59,616 --> 00:35:00,535
<i>Eva...</i>

353
00:35:02,071 --> 00:35:03,572
Do you want to call her?

354
00:35:10,863 --> 00:35:12,363
Shall I call her?

355
00:35:18,346 --> 00:35:20,445
Shall we visit the grave tomorrow?

356
00:35:26,987 --> 00:35:27,999
<i>No,</i>

357
00:35:28,804 --> 00:35:31,034
<i>first I have to
kill that bastard.</i>

358
00:35:57,744 --> 00:35:59,656
"BLUE DRAGON"

359
00:36:01,860 --> 00:36:03,262
Well?

360
00:36:03,472 --> 00:36:05,214
<i>I haven't tasted it yet.</i>

361
00:36:06,819 --> 00:36:08,947
"BLUE DRAGON"

362
00:36:11,904 --> 00:36:12,943
So?

363
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:16,239
Did it taste the same?

364
00:36:29,454 --> 00:36:32,243
<i>I could taste food from
100 restaurants...</i>

365
00:36:34,779 --> 00:36:37,818
<i>...but I will never forget the
food I tasted for 15 years.</i>

366
00:36:44,951 --> 00:36:46,449
"BLUE DRAGON"

367
00:37:06,157 --> 00:37:08,657
Shall I create an ID for you,
so you can log in?

368
00:37:09,406 --> 00:37:11,864
Do you have a favourite
film or song?

369
00:37:13,612 --> 00:37:17,658
I've already been talking...

370
00:37:18,307 --> 00:37:19,886
...to him...

371
00:37:27,425 --> 00:37:29,196
"The Count of Monte Cristo"?

372
00:37:31,404 --> 00:37:36,699
There's no one by that name here.

373
00:37:46,099 --> 00:37:48,737
"HOW'S LIFE IN A BIGGER PRISON,
OH DAE-SU?"

374
00:37:48,985 --> 00:37:50,115
Who are you?

375
00:37:53,148 --> 00:37:56,065
Who are you?

376
00:37:57,405 --> 00:37:59,456
"THE LONELY PRINCE IN THE HIGH TOWER."

377
00:37:59,526 --> 00:38:00,565
Who is he?

378
00:38:06,529 --> 00:38:09,526
I don't know who he is.
I just chat to him sometimes.

379
00:38:10,147 --> 00:38:11,776
We talk about sushi.

380
00:38:22,091 --> 00:38:23,340
Where are you going?

381
00:38:31,402 --> 00:38:32,533
Where are you going?

382
00:38:32,901 --> 00:38:34,401
You are not to be trusted.

383
00:38:51,114 --> 00:38:52,913
- VIOL...
- BLUE DRAGON

384
00:38:52,923 --> 00:38:58,197
Violet Blue Dragon...
What does that mean?

385
00:39:10,865 --> 00:39:13,362
<i>Why did they order
from a place so far away?</i>

386
00:39:14,861 --> 00:39:17,488
<i>I've already passed
five Chinese restaurants.</i>

387
00:39:20,193 --> 00:39:22,863
<i>I think my lungs are on
the verge of exploding.</i>

388
00:39:29,736 --> 00:39:34,281
You there, tell your cooks to put
less scallions in the dumplings.

389
00:39:35,730 --> 00:39:36,729
OK.

390
00:39:47,988 --> 00:39:49,776
- Leave it there and go.
- Yes, sir.

391
00:40:27,549 --> 00:40:31,364
We don't take on anyone
who uses bodyguards.

392
00:40:31,555 --> 00:40:33,652
Some companies specialize in that.

393
00:40:34,571 --> 00:40:36,069
You should go to them.

394
00:40:36,989 --> 00:40:39,776
We just take the small fry.

395
00:40:41,055 --> 00:40:44,781
If the stay is over six months,
transportation is free.

396
00:40:45,490 --> 00:40:47,528
Yes, of course.

397
00:40:54,031 --> 00:40:55,820
Why did you imprison me, you...

398
00:40:58,443 --> 00:41:00,235
...dickshit.

399
00:41:01,944 --> 00:41:07,858
In our business on floor 7Â½,
client confidentiality is our livelihood.

400
00:41:27,028 --> 00:41:29,736
I am going to avenge
myself for all 15 years.

401
00:41:30,964 --> 00:41:34,151
Each tooth I extract
will age you by one year.

402
00:41:50,164 --> 00:41:51,234
Keep still.

403
00:41:59,326 --> 00:42:00,615
Do you want to talk?

404
00:42:22,443 --> 00:42:24,569
I don't know...

405
00:42:24,571 --> 00:42:27,430
I don't know... I didn't see his face...

406
00:42:27,432 --> 00:42:30,279
I don't know... I didn't see his face... I made recordings...

407
00:42:44,011 --> 00:42:45,510
"OH DAE-SU"

408
00:42:51,574 --> 00:42:54,281
All those who are blood-type AB,
raise your hand.

409
00:43:07,389 --> 00:43:09,906
Go. Shoo!
He has lost a lot of blood.

410
00:44:02,993 --> 00:44:04,151
Piece of shit.

411
00:44:09,387 --> 00:44:10,865
Is he dead?

412
00:46:40,195 --> 00:46:41,864
I can't seem to...

413
00:46:42,493 --> 00:46:44,861
get through today either.

414
00:46:46,619 --> 00:46:50,285
Now I have become a monster.

415
00:46:51,864 --> 00:46:53,782
When my vengeance is over...

416
00:46:55,070 --> 00:46:56,909
...can I return to Oh Dae-su?

417
00:47:02,693 --> 00:47:05,900
Mister, are you alright?

418
00:47:05,902 --> 00:47:08,737
Look at all this blood.

419
00:47:10,321 --> 00:47:12,029
What happened to you?

420
00:47:17,469 --> 00:47:20,695
Saewoon Apartments, Eung-am,
building 8. Take care of him.

421
00:47:22,440 --> 00:47:23,521
Thank you.

422
00:47:24,031 --> 00:47:25,360
Not at all.

423
00:47:26,279 --> 00:47:28,277
Well, then...

424
00:47:29,616 --> 00:47:30,865
Farewell, Oh Dae-su.

425
00:47:34,861 --> 00:47:35,910
<i>Farewell...</i>

426
00:47:37,298 --> 00:47:38,877
<i>...Oh Dae-su.</i>

427
00:47:40,405 --> 00:47:41,444
<i>Farewell.</i>

428
00:47:43,402 --> 00:47:44,611
<i>Farewell.</i>

429
00:48:41,334 --> 00:48:43,502
The bastard you hate,
but don't dare kill.

430
00:48:43,736 --> 00:48:46,741
The bitch you detest, who
deserves a fate worse than death.

431
00:48:46,743 --> 00:48:48,321
We are at your service.

432
00:48:50,035 --> 00:48:53,032
Won't he go crazy if he's
locked up for a long time?

433
00:48:53,034 --> 00:48:58,069
Well, if you don't want that,
we can drug his drinks.

434
00:48:58,475 --> 00:49:01,129
There's a thing called
'Risterdal solution'.

435
00:49:01,131 --> 00:49:04,628
It's a reliable drug used
to treat schizophrenia.

436
00:49:05,934 --> 00:49:09,140
But it depends on the
length of the treatment,

437
00:49:09,482 --> 00:49:11,918
so how long will he...

438
00:49:11,920 --> 00:49:12,969
15 years.

439
00:49:15,338 --> 00:49:16,850
Is that possible?

440
00:49:16,852 --> 00:49:18,770
What did he do?

441
00:49:19,536 --> 00:49:21,114
Oh Dae-su, you see...

442
00:49:22,443 --> 00:49:24,491
...talks too much.

443
00:49:26,953 --> 00:49:27,908
Go to sleep.

444
00:49:29,137 --> 00:49:32,323
Tomorrow, you will visit
Joo-hwan's internet cafe.

445
00:49:42,695 --> 00:49:44,661
Sit wherever you like.

446
00:49:47,030 --> 00:49:48,027
Joo-hwan.

447
00:49:59,906 --> 00:50:01,364
Oh Dae-su, you see...

448
00:50:02,273 --> 00:50:03,902
...talks too much.

449
00:50:08,407 --> 00:50:10,485
Have you heard this voice before?

450
00:50:11,555 --> 00:50:13,702
Who loathes me this much?

451
00:50:21,154 --> 00:50:23,668
Those 260 women you've had...

452
00:50:23,670 --> 00:50:27,859
I don't know the names
of their husbands...

453
00:50:27,861 --> 00:50:31,224
"LOGON: MONSTER"

454
00:50:37,072 --> 00:50:38,827
"MIDO."

455
00:50:41,404 --> 00:50:43,173
Who's Mido?

456
00:50:43,175 --> 00:50:45,043
A little girl who cries a lot.

457
00:50:49,486 --> 00:50:50,535
Joo-hwan...

458
00:50:53,492 --> 00:50:54,531
Did I...

459
00:50:55,700 --> 00:50:57,368
...really talk too much?

460
00:51:01,175 --> 00:51:02,243
My friend...

461
00:51:02,296 --> 00:51:04,634
Maybe you should...

462
00:51:06,008 --> 00:51:10,285
...look for the criminal
among people you're close to.

463
00:51:12,777 --> 00:51:15,700
"SEARCH: EVERGREEN"

464
00:51:21,357 --> 00:51:22,493
"CHAT TO EVERGREEN?"

465
00:51:26,959 --> 00:51:30,675
"CONGRATULATIONS, YOUR CASE WAS
AUTOMATICALLY DISMISSED YESTERDAY."

466
00:51:30,677 --> 00:51:32,435
But please remember this...

467
00:51:33,612 --> 00:51:34,821
Open quote.

468
00:51:36,739 --> 00:51:39,786
Like a gazelle from the
hand of the hunter...

469
00:51:39,946 --> 00:51:43,032
Like a bird from the
snare of the fowler...

470
00:51:44,262 --> 00:51:45,700
Free yourself.

471
00:51:49,616 --> 00:51:51,034
Close quote.

472
00:51:52,485 --> 00:51:54,531
Who are you? You bastard!

473
00:51:55,929 --> 00:51:58,077
I decided when I was a prisoner...

474
00:51:58,453 --> 00:52:00,875
that if I got out,
I would trust no one.

475
00:52:01,244 --> 00:52:03,612
If I met anyone suspicious,

476
00:52:03,824 --> 00:52:06,489
I would invent a secret,
only known to the two of us.

477
00:52:08,027 --> 00:52:11,154
That ID, Monster, is a trap
I designed to catch him.

478
00:52:12,241 --> 00:52:14,821
You let a stranger into your home.
Who are you?

479
00:52:25,366 --> 00:52:26,659
Who's Evergreen?

480
00:52:34,682 --> 00:52:38,867
I tracked down that Evergreen ID
and found the owner's details.

481
00:52:38,869 --> 00:52:41,194
- Are you ready to jot it down?
- Go ahead.

482
00:52:41,404 --> 00:52:44,679
It's Su Dae-oh.
Does the surname 'Su' even exist?

483
00:52:44,681 --> 00:52:48,207
- Address?
- Saewoon Apartments in Eung-am.

484
00:52:48,209 --> 00:52:49,708
Building 7, flat 407.

485
00:52:55,181 --> 00:52:57,276
<i>Actually, life in a bigger prison</i>

486
00:52:57,278 --> 00:52:59,576
<i>does not suit me very well.</i>

487
00:53:18,277 --> 00:53:19,576
Evergreen.

488
00:53:21,444 --> 00:53:22,653
Who are you?

489
00:53:27,408 --> 00:53:29,076
Is that what you wanted to ask?

490
00:53:30,695 --> 00:53:33,662
No. You must find that
out for yourself.

491
00:53:33,664 --> 00:53:35,001
Come on, it's a game.

492
00:53:36,119 --> 00:53:39,156
First " who?".
Then "why?".

493
00:53:40,235 --> 00:53:42,453
When you know the answer,
come and see me.

494
00:53:42,865 --> 00:53:44,651
I'll mark your work.

495
00:53:44,653 --> 00:53:46,529
You have until July 5th.

496
00:53:48,617 --> 00:53:50,995
Oh no, only five days left.

497
00:53:53,742 --> 00:53:54,781
Too short?

498
00:53:56,029 --> 00:53:57,086
Chin up.

499
00:53:57,679 --> 00:54:00,825
If you succeed,
I'll kill myself instead of Mido.

500
00:54:04,241 --> 00:54:05,700
That's right.

501
00:54:06,409 --> 00:54:10,825
I'm going to kill every woman
you love until you die.

502
00:54:12,903 --> 00:54:16,569
Well, you're notorious for not
protecting your women anyway.

503
00:54:23,572 --> 00:54:26,869
Wow, you're strong, Mr. Monster.

504
00:54:27,988 --> 00:54:30,235
Yes, you are the monster
that I created.

505
