What are you doing?

767
01:22:29,941 --> 01:22:31,109
Let me see.

768
01:22:31,111 --> 01:22:32,400
What are you doing?

769
01:22:33,502 --> 01:22:35,260
- Let me see.
- Stop it!

770
01:22:46,384 --> 01:22:47,683
Go away.

771
01:24:29,612 --> 01:24:31,940
Was it really Soo-ah? Are you sure?

772
01:24:32,783 --> 01:24:34,321
I don't know her name.

773
01:24:35,123 --> 01:24:39,129
I just know that she's in your
class and she rides a red bike.

774
01:24:47,072 --> 01:24:49,740
Have a good trip.
See you in Seoul.

775
01:24:49,926 --> 01:24:51,384
Where are you going?

776
01:24:51,386 --> 01:24:53,424
I've got a date with Choon-shim.

777
01:24:54,606 --> 01:24:56,564
I'll kill you if you blab to anyone.

778
01:25:01,790 --> 01:25:02,829
No way.

779
01:25:04,844 --> 01:25:08,260
You got locked up for 15 years
just for saying that?

780
01:25:10,965 --> 01:25:12,673
Is that such a crime?

781
01:25:15,586 --> 01:25:18,365
"Whether it be a grain
of sand or a rock,

782
01:25:18,367 --> 01:25:20,405
in water they both sink alike."

783
01:25:23,891 --> 01:25:25,969
That's Lee Woo-jin's attitude.

784
01:25:28,071 --> 01:25:29,490
So,

785
01:25:30,129 --> 01:25:32,087
what's the significance of July 5th?

786
01:25:33,588 --> 01:25:35,126
That's the day...

787
01:25:38,102 --> 01:25:39,771
...Lee Soo-ah died.

788
01:25:45,291 --> 01:25:47,049
It's over now.

789
01:25:47,591 --> 01:25:49,700
You were fighting for the truth,

790
01:25:49,702 --> 01:25:51,818
not for revenge, weren't you?

791
01:25:54,471 --> 01:25:58,387
Now, we'll run away where
Woo-jin can never follow us.

792
01:26:02,280 --> 01:26:03,689
<i>I can't end it like this.</i>

793
01:26:04,680 --> 01:26:07,097
Vengeance has become a part of me.

794
01:26:12,744 --> 01:26:15,451
But you don't even
know where he lives.

795
01:26:16,942 --> 01:26:20,318
<i>"Like a gazelle from the
hand of the hunter...</i>

796
01:26:20,320 --> 01:26:23,527
<i>"Like a bird from the
snare of the fowler...</i>

797
01:26:23,872 --> 01:26:24,951
<i>"Free yourself. "</i>

798
01:26:26,304 --> 01:26:30,720
<i>It is taken from the Book of Proverbs,
chapter six, verse four.</i>

799
01:26:30,977 --> 01:26:32,315
<i>And Evergreen...</i>

800
01:26:33,320 --> 01:26:35,198
<i>...said he lives in a high tower.</i>

801
01:26:36,409 --> 01:26:38,737
<i>So six and four...</i>

802
01:26:39,901 --> 01:26:41,189
<i>...must be floors.</i>

803
01:26:42,648 --> 01:26:43,687
<i>Fourth floor.</i>

804
01:26:45,037 --> 01:26:46,416
<i>Sixth floor.</i>

805
01:26:47,320 --> 01:26:48,739
<i>Or the 64th floor?</i>

806
01:26:51,791 --> 01:26:52,840
<i>P?</i>

807
01:26:53,464 --> 01:26:54,753
<i>Penthouse!</i>

808
01:26:58,120 --> 01:27:00,248
Please insert the code.

809
01:27:06,839 --> 01:27:09,486
What would you like me to pray for?

810
01:27:12,275 --> 01:27:13,524
Wrong entry.

811
01:27:14,223 --> 01:27:16,261
Please re-enter.

812
01:27:21,374 --> 01:27:24,971
Wrong entry. Please re-enter.

813
01:27:25,370 --> 01:27:26,419
"Dear Lord...

814
01:27:28,655 --> 01:27:30,073
...please let me...

815
01:27:31,485 --> 01:27:33,903
...meet a younger man next time."

816
01:28:24,199 --> 01:28:25,958
Please make Woo-jin...

817
01:28:27,146 --> 01:28:28,855
...kneel before Dae-su...

818
01:28:30,548 --> 01:28:33,375
...and beg for forgiveness.

819
01:28:47,110 --> 01:28:48,739
You slept with your sister.

820
01:29:00,181 --> 01:29:01,850
Let's go upstairs and talk.

821
01:29:25,142 --> 01:29:26,231
Get him!

822
01:29:49,113 --> 01:29:51,281
Just talk.

823
01:30:22,117 --> 01:30:23,656
That's better.

824
01:30:25,812 --> 01:30:27,480
You slept with your sister.

825
01:30:27,638 --> 01:30:28,887
So refreshing.

826
01:30:35,627 --> 01:30:38,044
And I started the rumours.

827
01:30:39,025 --> 01:30:40,734
That's why your sister died.

828
01:30:48,281 --> 01:30:51,118
Looking in the mirror
reminds me of that day.

829
01:30:52,142 --> 01:30:53,214
How about you?

830
01:30:53,216 --> 01:30:57,432
Erasing my memory and telling
me to find the truth was cowardly.

831
01:30:59,111 --> 01:31:00,400
I won...

832
01:31:02,809 --> 01:31:04,727
...so die like you promised.

833
01:31:04,883 --> 01:31:08,349
Did you think you'd forgotten that
day because you were hypnotized?

834
01:31:10,013 --> 01:31:10,893
Really?

835
01:31:12,586 --> 01:31:15,503
Do you know the real reason
why you can't remember?

836
01:31:18,842 --> 01:31:19,961
It's because...

837
01:31:24,412 --> 01:31:25,871
...you just forgot.

838
01:31:26,775 --> 01:31:28,787
Is that not exciting enough for you?

839
01:31:29,490 --> 01:31:32,537
Well, it's true, you just forgot.

840
01:31:32,944 --> 01:31:35,531
Why? Because it wasn't
important to you.

841
01:31:36,860 --> 01:31:38,769
Your rumour got so out of hand,

842
01:31:38,771 --> 01:31:42,057
that the next rumour was
that Soo-ah was pregnant.

843
01:31:42,343 --> 01:31:46,799
My sister got sucked into that
rumour and began believing it.

844
01:31:47,287 --> 01:31:50,954
So her periods stopped
and her belly began to swell.

845
01:31:52,093 --> 01:31:53,632
Fascinating, isn't it?

846
01:31:53,870 --> 01:31:57,616
Imagine how a girl would feel to
carry both her child and her nephew.

847
01:31:57,988 --> 01:31:59,526
Do you understand now?

848
01:32:00,705 --> 01:32:04,531
Your tongue got my sister pregnant.

849
01:32:06,719 --> 01:32:08,847
It wasn't Lee Woo-jin's dick.

850
01:32:10,585 --> 01:32:11,954
It was Oh Dae-su's tongue.

851
01:32:17,782 --> 01:32:19,700
Is that why you killed your sister?

852
01:32:20,175 --> 01:32:24,131
Imagine how a boy would feel,
fathering both his child and his nephew?

853
01:32:28,531 --> 01:32:29,990
You were probably afraid.

854
01:32:30,598 --> 01:32:33,635
Afraid that everyone would know
once the baby was born.

855
01:32:35,291 --> 01:32:38,708
After you killed her, you realised
it was a phantom pregnancy...

856
01:32:40,002 --> 01:32:41,630
...so your hating me...

857
01:32:43,763 --> 01:32:44,826
...is understandable.

858
01:32:50,304 --> 01:32:52,672
They said Soo-ah
died alone at the dam,

859
01:32:53,545 --> 01:32:54,924
so who took this photo?

860
01:32:56,755 --> 01:32:58,633
And what about the date, July 5th?

861
01:33:06,279 --> 01:33:08,617
This is no fun.

862
01:33:09,552 --> 01:33:11,880
I'll just finish what I was saying.

863
01:33:12,487 --> 01:33:15,194
Listen carefully.
My story is really exciting.

864
01:33:15,704 --> 01:33:18,168
Ever heard of
post-hypnotic suggestion?

865
01:33:18,170 --> 01:33:20,564
You suggest something
during hypnosis,

866
01:33:20,566 --> 01:33:22,814
then it's performed
in your wakened state.

867
01:33:24,718 --> 01:33:26,426
Still haven't worked it out?

868
01:33:32,982 --> 01:33:36,169
You let a stranger into your home.
Who are you?

869
01:33:36,348 --> 01:33:38,941
<i>What about you, you bastard?</i>

870
01:33:44,282 --> 01:33:46,820
We hypnotized both of you.

871
01:33:48,442 --> 01:33:54,368
One fortunate thing was that, compared to others,
both of you were receptive to hypnosis.

872
01:33:56,258 --> 01:33:57,547
Isn't this fun?

873
01:33:57,690 --> 01:34:01,816
One word gets you pregnant.
Another makes you fall in love.

874
01:34:04,895 --> 01:34:09,319
But no matter how receptive
you two were to hypnosis,

875
01:34:09,321 --> 01:34:12,651
and no matter how good
a hypnotist Miss Yoo is,

876
01:34:12,653 --> 01:34:15,900
getting people to
fall in love isn't easy.

877
01:34:18,093 --> 01:34:19,512
Do you know how we did it?

878
01:34:23,031 --> 01:34:25,535
Your first suggestion, of course,

879
01:34:25,537 --> 01:34:27,535
was to go to that restaurant

880
01:34:27,537 --> 01:34:30,124
straight after your release.

881
01:34:31,448 --> 01:34:34,535
Next, to react to the
mobile phone's ringtone.

882
01:34:35,793 --> 01:34:39,839
When you heard this,
you were programmed to say something.

883
01:34:41,263 --> 01:34:42,302
Who are you?

884
01:34:44,270 --> 01:34:47,517
Do you... like your clothes?

885
01:34:48,625 --> 01:34:53,540
And Mido was programmed to react
to the man who would say this.

886
01:34:53,894 --> 01:34:57,440
When she touched your hand,
your reaction would be...

887
01:35:01,514 --> 01:35:04,601
Your gravest mistake wasn't
failing to find the answer.

888
01:35:05,680 --> 01:35:11,372
If you keep asking the wrong questions,
you'll never find the right answer.

889
01:35:11,374 --> 01:35:15,960
It's not,
"Why did Woo-jin imprison me?"

890
01:35:16,466 --> 01:35:19,113
It's "Why did he release me?"

891
01:35:19,367 --> 01:35:21,235
Once again...

892
01:35:22,241 --> 01:35:26,317
...why did Woo-jin
release Dae-su after...

893
01:35:28,307 --> 01:35:29,506
...15 years?

894
01:37:31,324 --> 01:37:34,721
"LAUGH, AND THE WORLD LAUGHS WITH YOU.
WEEP, AND YOU WEEP ALONE."

895
01:39:15,725 --> 01:39:17,013
Mr. Han.

896
01:39:25,797 --> 01:39:27,295
Mr. Han!

897
01:40:08,034 --> 01:40:09,283
Mido...

898
01:40:16,185 --> 01:40:17,554
Mido doesn't know?

899
01:40:22,880 --> 01:40:24,928
Why did you hide her there?

900
01:40:26,850 --> 01:40:30,096
Did you think he'd hate me
just because I cut off his hand?

901
01:40:30,492 --> 01:40:32,650
Didn't you work out
that it was a trap?

902
01:40:35,058 --> 01:40:38,265
How can you protect your
woman with that brain?

903
01:40:39,806 --> 01:40:43,632
I've secretly been raising
Mido since she was three.

904
01:40:44,978 --> 01:40:46,976
What's wrong with you?

905
01:40:48,161 --> 01:40:49,790
Mr. Park's hand?

906
01:40:51,294 --> 01:40:52,983
You moron.

907
01:40:53,998 --> 01:40:58,445
Did you see his new prison?
I gave him that building for his hand!

908
01:40:58,447 --> 01:40:59,656
ME!

909
01:41:24,460 --> 01:41:25,669
Dae-su!

910
01:41:27,755 --> 01:41:31,952
In front of me there's
some kind of box.

911
01:41:31,954 --> 01:41:33,782
He's telling me to open it.

912
01:41:34,492 --> 01:41:36,167
It's the same violet box...

913
01:41:36,169 --> 01:41:37,128
NO!

914
01:41:38,304 --> 01:41:43,346
No, Mido, don't.
Don't open it, no matter what.

915
01:41:43,348 --> 01:41:45,807
Or something terrible will happen.

916
01:41:45,809 --> 01:41:47,158
What's in it?

917
01:41:48,071 --> 01:41:49,476
You know, don't you?

918
01:41:49,478 --> 01:41:52,560
Mido, just wait a little longer.

919
01:41:52,562 --> 01:41:57,487
Dae-su will be there soon.
I'll be there very soon.

920
01:41:59,526 --> 01:42:01,734
Can't you come now?

921
01:42:04,201 --> 01:42:05,410
I'm scared.

922
01:42:05,732 --> 01:42:07,920
Little Mido, you can wait, can't you?

923
01:42:07,922 --> 01:42:09,040
Yes.

924
01:42:09,741 --> 01:42:12,028
Very good. Good girl.

925
01:42:13,301 --> 01:42:16,928
I'll call you back very soon, OK?

926
01:42:32,133 --> 01:42:33,182
Please.

927
01:42:36,604 --> 01:42:38,312
Don't tell Mido.

928
01:42:43,010 --> 01:42:44,679
What has she done wrong?

929
01:42:47,198 --> 01:42:48,747
You know it was all my fault.

930
01:42:52,876 --> 01:42:54,244
I have...

931
01:42:55,892 --> 01:42:58,059
...committed an unforgivable sin...

932
01:42:59,011 --> 01:43:00,800
...against your sister!

933
01:43:02,684 --> 01:43:04,762
And I also...

934
01:43:06,155 --> 01:43:07,524
...did you wrong.

935
01:43:09,283 --> 01:43:10,332
But...

936
01:43:12,206 --> 01:43:14,503
...please leave Mido alone.

937
01:43:20,140 --> 01:43:21,179
If by any chance...

938
01:43:22,678 --> 01:43:24,676
...Mido finds out the truth,

939
01:43:25,728 --> 01:43:27,726
you son of a bitch,

940
01:43:28,287 --> 01:43:31,914
I'll tear you limb from limb!

941
01:43:32,801 --> 01:43:37,181
And your remains will never be found.

942
01:43:37,492 --> 01:43:38,771
Why?

943
01:43:38,959 --> 01:43:41,626
Because I'm going to
swallow every last bit.

944
01:43:44,277 --> 01:43:45,396
Woo-jin!

945
01:43:46,358 --> 01:43:48,816
Please, sir, I made a mistake.

946
01:43:48,818 --> 01:43:51,905
Please forget what I said.

947
01:43:52,115 --> 01:43:54,443
Sir! Woo-jin!

948
01:43:54,445 --> 01:43:59,368
We're Evergreen Old Boys, remember?

949
01:44:00,968 --> 01:44:07,011
With the energy
of a green pine tree

950
01:44:10,034 --> 01:44:14,500
The Great Sangnok High...

951
01:44:17,198 --> 01:44:20,260
I'll do whatever you want.

952
01:44:20,575 --> 01:44:22,703
I'll do anything. I beg you.

953
01:44:23,506 --> 01:44:28,823
Woo-jin, if you want me
to be your dog, I will!

954
01:44:28,825 --> 01:44:32,571
From this moment on,
I am Woo-jin's dog!

955
01:44:32,573 --> 01:44:34,111
I'm your bitch.

956
01:44:40,521 --> 01:44:42,679
Look, I'm wagging my tail.

957
01:44:43,326 --> 01:44:46,327
I'm a dog. I'll guard your house.

958
01:44:46,329 --> 01:44:48,947
I'll be your slave.

959
01:46:56,613 --> 01:46:58,071
The box...

960
01:47:03,702 --> 01:47:05,120
...just leave it closed.

961
01:47:16,092 --> 01:47:17,141
Now...

962
01:47:20,226 --> 01:47:22,524
...what will I live for?

963
01:48:25,250 --> 01:48:26,419
Dae-su.

964
01:48:26,829 --> 01:48:28,497
It hurts so much.

965
01:48:29,383 --> 01:48:31,211
But I'll endure it.

966
01:48:32,306 --> 01:48:33,675
You must understand.

967
01:48:57,898 --> 01:49:01,184
My sister and I loved each other,
despite everything.

968
01:49:05,673 --> 01:49:07,341
Can you two do the same?

969
01:49:51,054 --> 01:49:52,093
Soo-ah.

970
01:50:07,523 --> 01:50:08,722
Woo-jin.

971
01:50:10,624 --> 01:50:12,622
I know you've always been afraid.

972
01:50:15,459 --> 01:50:18,206
So just let go of me.

973
01:50:35,200 --> 01:50:38,077
Please remember me.

974
01:50:46,597 --> 01:50:49,304
I have no regrets. Do you?

975
01:51:34,880 --> 01:51:37,829
<i>This is the whole adventure
of my life until now.</i>

976
01:51:38,762 --> 01:51:42,298
<i>Thank you for listening to
this terrible story to the end.</i>

977
01:51:43,153 --> 01:51:47,569
<i>I trust that you will
understand my sending a letter</i>

978
01:51:47,571 --> 01:51:50,682
<i>instead of talking to you in person.</i>

979
01:51:51,336 --> 01:51:53,340
<i>This is because
I have no tongue.</i>

980
01:51:53,342 --> 01:51:56,350
To be honest,
there's no reason I should help you.

981
01:52:02,051 --> 01:52:03,430
But there was one thing.

982
01:52:04,704 --> 01:52:06,992
I was touched by this last sentence.

983
01:52:08,896 --> 01:52:14,215
"EVEN THOUGH I'M NO BETTER THAN A BEAST,

984
01:52:14,216 --> 01:52:18,402
DON'T I HAVE THE RIGHT TO LIVE?"

985
01:52:21,282 --> 01:52:24,279
The hypnosis may go wrong
and distort your memories.

986
01:52:26,175 --> 01:52:27,464
Do you want to proceed?

987
01:52:48,680 --> 01:52:50,508
If you're ready...

988
01:52:52,355 --> 01:52:54,353
...look at that tree.

989
01:53:11,288 --> 01:53:12,537
The tree...

990
01:53:13,582 --> 01:53:16,629
...is slowly changing
into a concrete pillar.

991
01:53:25,269 --> 01:53:29,185
You're now inside
Lee Woo-jin's penthouse.

992
01:53:30,326 --> 01:53:31,985
It's a dreary night.

993
01:53:35,276 --> 01:53:40,071
The sound of your footsteps crossing
to the window fills the room.

994
01:53:54,202 --> 01:53:57,739
When I ring my bell...

995
01:53:59,167 --> 01:54:02,044
...you'll split into two people.

996
01:54:06,178 --> 01:54:09,555
One person doesn't know
your secret: Oh Dae-su.

997
01:54:10,811 --> 01:54:13,638
The one who knows your
secret is the monster.

998
01:54:15,090 --> 01:54:20,131
When I ring the bell again, the monster
will turn around and start walking.

999
01:54:25,448 --> 01:54:31,242
With each step,
he will age by one year.

1000
01:54:31,592 --> 01:54:34,432
When he reaches 70,
the monster will die.

1001
01:54:34,996 --> 01:54:36,494
There's no need to worry.

1002
01:54:37,350 --> 01:54:40,057
It will be a very peaceful death.

1003
01:54:47,797 --> 01:54:49,305
Now, good luck to you.

1004
01:55:32,023 --> 01:55:34,071
What's going on?

1005
01:55:35,011 --> 01:55:37,049
Look at you.

1006
01:56:06,148 --> 01:56:07,777
Who were you with?

1007
01:57:03,635 --> 01:57:05,133
I love you...

1008
01:57:06,265 --> 01:57:07,514
...Dae-su...
